Patch Set 2: -Code-Review

It would be confusing to change the CFS_HASH_ALG_SHA* to be HMAC's instead.  What about just adding CFS_HMAC_ALG_SHA256 and CFS_HMAC_ALG_SHA512 in addition to the hash algorithms?

        [CFS_HMAC_ALG_SHA256] = { 
                .cht_name       = "hmac(sha256)",
                .cht_key        = 0,
                .cht_size       = 32
        },
        [CFS_HMAC_ALG_SHA512] = { 
                .cht_name       = "hmac(sha512)",
                .cht_key        = 0,
                .cht_size       = 64
        },

I haven't really looked closely here but at least in libcfs_crypto.h I didn't see a problem with it.

Patch Set 3: -Code-Review

> Is this strictly user land code that is broken or is kernel
 > communicate going on?

The user land lgss_sk command seems to be failing in sk_validate_config():
...
if ((config->skc_hmac_alg != CFS_HASH_ALG_SHA256) &&
            (config->skc_hmac_alg != CFS_HASH_ALG_SHA512)) {
                printerr(0, "Invalid HMAC algorithm\n");
                return -1;
        }

Should the tests be OR'd and checked against CFS_HMAC_ALG_SHA256 and CFS_HMAC_ALG_SHA512 instead?
